label.value: Interchanged Precordial Electrodes by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which two or more of the precordial electrodes are switched resulting in improper representation of the affected leads. (CDISC)

label.value: Disconnected Precordial Electrode V1 by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which the electrode for lead V1 is disconnected resulting in missing waveforms (flat line) for lead V1. (CDISC)

label.value: Disconnected Precordial Electrode V2 by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which the electrode for lead V2 is disconnected resulting in missing waveforms (flat line) for lead V2. (CDISC)

label.value: Disconnected Precordial Electrode V3 by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which the electrode for lead V3 is disconnected resulting in missing waveforms (flat line) for lead V3. (CDISC)

label.value: Disconnected Precordial Electrode V4 by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which the electrode for lead V4 is disconnected resulting in missing waveforms (flat line) for lead V4. (CDISC)

label.value: Disconnected Precordial Electrode V5 by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which the electrode for lead V5 is disconnected resulting in missing waveforms (flat line) for lead V5. (CDISC)

label.value: Disconnected Precordial Electrode V6 by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which the electrode for lead V6 is disconnected resulting in missing waveforms (flat line) for lead V6. (CDISC)

label.value: All Precordial Electrodes Are Disconnected by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which all precordial electrodes are disconnected resulting in missing waveforms (flat line) of all leads V1 - V6. (CDISC)

label.value: Fluorouracil/Paclitaxel
Incorrectly Positioned Precordial Electrodes by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which one or more precordial electrodes are placed incorrectly with respect to the standard chest electrode positions resulting in improper representation of the affected leads. (CDISC)

label.value: Quality Problem Not Otherwise Specified by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic artifact or recording error with unknown origin or which is not described otherwise. (CDISC)

label.value: Artifact Lead Signal by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which one or more leads display extraneous signals which do not represent cardiac electrical activity. (CDISC)

label.value: ECG Waveforms Not Present

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording that displays flat lines (no waveforms are visible) in all leads present. (CDISC)

label.value: 60 Hertz Noise by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording showing power line interference with the electrocardiographic signal. The artifact amplitude modulation has the same frequency as the AC power system present (60 Hz). (CDISC)

label.value: 50 Hertz Noise by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording showing power line interference with the electrocardiographic signal. The artifact amplitude modulation has the same frequency as the AC power system present (50 Hz). (CDISC)

label.value: Low Amplitude QRS Complex by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording showing smaller than usual QRS complexes in one or more leads. This may represent a technical issue with the ECG acquisition or characteristics of the individual. (CDISC)

label.value: Incomplete ECG

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording which is limited in duration or which does not display all of the expected leads. (CDISC)

label.value: Incorrectly Scaled ECG

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which the ECG signal is not displayed at the indicated recording speed and/or amplitude resolution. (CDISC)

label.value: Incompletely Digitized ECG Leads

value.value: A digital electrocardiographic recording which was digitized from paper ECG tracings and which does not contain all leads present on the original paper printout. (CDISC)

label.value: Bryostatin 1/Fludarabine
Inability to Digitize ECG Leads

value.value: A statement indicating the inability to digitize a paper ECG. (CDISC)

label.value: Invalid ECG Waveforms

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording for which the displayed leads do not represent the individual's true ECG lead information. (CDISC)

label.value: Poor Quality ECG

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording that does not show proper quality for reasons that are not otherwise described. (CDISC)

label.value: Suspicion of Limb Electrodes Reversal But Interpretation Assumes No Reversal by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which an interchange of one or more limb lead electrodes is suspected, but for which an interpretation is performed as though the lead placement is correct. (CDISC)

label.value: Suspicion of Limb Electrodes Reversal But Interpretation Assumes Reversal by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which an interchange of one or more limb lead electrodes is suspected, and for which an interpretation is performed as though the leads have in fact been interchanged. (CDISC)

label.value: ECG Acquired with Precordial Electrodes Placed on the Right Chest

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which the precordial electrodes have been placed over the right chest and record a right sided ECG. (CDISC)

label.value: Other Incorrect Electrode Placement

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which one or more electrodes are incorrectly placed but further details are not provided. (CDISC)

label.value: Insufficient Number of Beats for Complete ECG Evaluation

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which fewer than the required number of cardiac complexes are available for measurement and/or interpretation due to a shorter than planned recording or due to cardiac complexes which are present but are not suitable for measurement and/or interpretation. (CDISC)

label.value: ECG Evaluation Not Performed Due to Unknown ECG Amplitude Gain or Recording Speed

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which measurements and/or interpretation are not performed because the ECG amplitude gain and/or recording speed are not known. (CDISC)

label.value: Incomplete ECG Measurements Due to Truncation of QRS Complexes

value.value: An electrocardiographic recording in which measurements (particularly of QRS amplitudes) and/or interpretations are not performed because QRS complexes have been truncated. (CDISC)

label.value: BMS-182751/Prednisone
ECG Evaluation Not Performed Due to Poor Quality of Printed ECG

value.value: A printed electrocardiographic recording with poor printout quality (e.g. a faded paper ECG tracing or ECG with inconsistent printing speed) such that measurements and/or interpretation cannot be performed. (CDISC)

label.value: ECG Evaluation Not Performed Due to Corrupted Digital ECG File

value.value: A digital electrocardiographic recording which is corrupted (i.e. ECG signal cannot be restored) such that measurements and/or interpretation cannot be performed. (CDISC)

label.value: Dominant Hand

value.value: The preferred hand of use for controlled and efficient performance of motor tasks.

label.value: Boundary Shift Integral

value.value: A measurement of change in volume of an organ or anatomical feature as determined by a shift in tissue boundary over time.

label.value: MRI Without Contrast

value.value: A technique that uses radiofrequency waves and a magnet to image the body, in which the images are not enhanced by the addition of contrast agents.

label.value: Polysomnography

value.value: A group of tests taken during sleep to capture and record brain wave changes, eye movements, breathing rate, blood pressure, heart rate, and the electrical activity of the heart and other muscles.

label.value: Femoral Condyle

value.value: A rounded bony projection at the distal end of the femur.

label.value: Humeral Epicondyle

value.value: A bone prominence at the distal end of the humerus to which ligaments and tendons of the joints are attached.

label.value: Distal Interphalangeal Joint 2 of the Hand

value.value: A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint within the second digit of the hand connecting the middle and distal phalanges.

label.value: Distal Interphalangeal Joint 3 of the Hand

value.value: A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint within the third digit of the hand connecting the middle and distal phalanges.

label.value: Doxorubicin HCl Liposome/Etoposide
Interphalangeal Joint 2 of the Hand

value.value: A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint between the phalanges of the second digit of the hand.

label.value: Interphalangeal Joint 3 of the Hand

value.value: A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint between the phalanges of the third digit of the hand.

label.value: Interphalangeal Joint 4 of the Hand

value.value: A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint between the phalanges of the fourth digit of the hand.

label.value: Interphalangeal Joint 5 of the Hand

value.value: A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint between the phalanges of the fifth digit of the hand.

label.value: Proximal Interphalangeal Joint 2 of the Hand

value.value: A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint within the second digit of the hand connecting the proximal and middle phalanges.

label.value: Proximal Interphalangeal Joint 3 of the Hand

value.value: A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint within the third digit of the hand connecting the proximal and middle phalanges.

label.value: Proximal Interphalangeal Joint 4 of the Hand

value.value: A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint within the fourth digit of the hand connecting the proximal and middle phalanges.
